Method Detail

parentFile

public IFile parentFile()
Description copied from interface: IFile
Returns the abstract pathname of this abstract pathname's parent, or null if this pathname does not name a parent directory.

The parent of an abstract pathname consists of the pathname's prefix, if any, and each name in the pathname's name sequence except for the last. If the name sequence is empty then the pathname does not name a parent directory.

Specified by:
parentFile in interface IFile
Returns:
The abstract pathname of the parent directory named by this abstract pathname, or null if this pathname does not name a parent

equals

public boolean equals(Object obj)
By default, File compares to another one by its pathname. So if two different File's have same pathname, they are equal. But to let the History works, we don't do that.
For example we have this history: 1-2-3-2-4-5, and it is used in a List, then if we use File, we will only get 1 for method List.indexOf(Object) with file "2". But we have 2 positions for "2".

So, we override this method :-) The result is a comparison of operator ==
